subSubSection.paragraph:
Posterior lobes fused for about 3/5 their length. BL1–2 as long as BL3–4. BL1–2 and BL5–6 with large lamellae, broad almost 3 times more than BL3–4; lamella of BL1–2 and BL3–4 with longitudinal ridges; outer edges of lamellae with a row of small rounded papilla; inside edges of lamellae smooth; without cilia (
Fig. 3D–G
); BL3–4 with small lamellae, without distal tip.

